Biography

2016 (Outdoor): Set a personal and season best in the 1500-meter run, finishing with a time of 5:49.71 at the KT Woodman Classic ... Ran a season best in the 800-meter run, finishing with a time of 2:38.04 at the MSSU Bill Williams/Bob Laptad Invite ... Earned a 10th-place finish in the 800-meter run at the SBU Bearcat Invite with a time of 2:38.21 ...

2015-16 (Indoor): Ran a season best in the 800-meter run, finishing with a time of 2:47.14 at the Indoor Gorilla Classic …

2015 (Outdoor): Set a personal and season best in the 800-meter run, finishing with a time of 2:30.37 at the Wichita State Shocker Open ... Ran a season best in the 1500-meter run, finishing with a time of 5:52.21 at the Wichita State Shocker Open ... Earned a ninth-place finish in the 800-meter run at the Tulsa Duels with a time of 2:32.29 ... Member of relay team that earned a fifth-place finish in the 4x400-meter relay at the Wendy's/PSU Invitational with a time of 4:21.93 ...

2014-15 (Indoor): Set a personal and season best in the 800-meter run, finishing with a time of 2:33.20 at the OBU Bison Invitational …

About: Buckner came to the Hill from Coweta High School as a two-time Oklahoma state team cross country champion. She competed on the Tigers' cross country and track and field teams for four years winning state titles in her first two seasons. She earned the Coweta Tiger Award during both her junior and senior campaigns. In the spring of 2013, as a junior, Buckner won the conference and regional championships in the 800 meters while placing sixth at the state meet. She also claimed a state championship in the 4x800 relay during her sophomore season. The daughter of Bill and Mary Buckner, she said she chose RSU because "RSU is my home away from home. I love the environment."
